div.div:
Pre-test setup:
1. ssh to host (HUT) with provided auth details (default port 22)
2. init container in HUT which runs sshd on exposed port and has required dependencies for tests (we control it).
3. disconnect from ssh connection (port 22) and ssh directly into running remote docker container

text-align: left

div.div: 1. Test is made up of layered plugins (infra - SSH, Devops - Memsql, Kafka Core - TracksDb, pipeng, camera_service, Teams - Api, Insights, etc)

div.style: text-align: left

div.div: 2. Each test writer can use their own plugins, and obv also all plugins underneath them

div.style: text-align: left
div.span: 3. Plugins tunnel their communication through the ssh connection (connection is between docker_local and docker_remote via port X, not regular SSH connection).

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; text-align: center;
div.div:
If running remotely, this is a loop, once for each test.
If running locally, the tests will run 1 after another
without setup/teardown of docker container
